The Arcadia Consortium 
 

The Arcadia project is organized as an informal consortium of separately
funded researchers.  These include the following academic institutions
and principal investigators:

  
Arcadia at University of California, Irvine (UCI)  

 
      Debra J. Richardson </strong> (djr@ics.uci.edu)
   Testing, Analysis
    Richard W. Selby</strong> (selby@ics.uci.edu)
   Measurement and Evaluation
      Richard N. Taylor </strong> (taylor@ics.uci.edu)
   Software Architecture, User Interface Software, Team-Support Software,
and Hypermedia
   

  
Arcadia at University of Colorado at Boulder (CU)  

 
      Dennis Heimbigner </strong> (dennis@cs.colorado.edu)
   Object Management, Process, Architecture
    Roger King</strong> (roger@cs.colorado.edu)
   Object Management
      Alexander L. Wolf </strong> (alw@cs.colorado.edu)
   Process, Analysis, Language Issues, Architecture
   

  
Arcadia at University of Massachusetts at Amherst (UMass)  

 
      Lori A. Clarke </strong> (clarke@cs.umass.edu)
   Object Management, Language Processing, Analysis
      Leon J. Osterweil </strong> (ljo@cs.umass.edu)
   Process, Architecture
   

  
Arcadia at Purdue University  

 
      Michal Young </strong> (young@cs.purdue.edu)
   Analysis
   

  
